While she was still at Sega Girls’ High School, Phoebe captained her school to the national finals of the secondary school games and won a number of personal accolades.
Think of how differently that story could have ended had she been equipped with a clear path of trajectory in her football career. Had she been enrolled in an academy where her skills could be properly nurtured and where she would remain engaged competitively so that she could reach her highest football potential. Perhaps she would now be earning top dollar while playing abroad and representing her country in the best possible way.
Now think of the goalkeeper with one torn glove and how difficult it will be for her to achieve her dreams. For her to even pursue her ambitions. With very few stable league teams and none that have any clear structures of nurturing young talent, our little goalie may never grow to become the next Karen Beardsley.
Watching her stretch in childlike fashion while struggling to catch the ball and flapping her hands funnily in anticipation, all the while laughing heartily with her friend, I found myself longing to see her in real action, standing in goal for self and country, having realized her dreams. I imagine she will grow both in physical stature and presence such that she will make the goal mouth look small.



